The paper discusses the impact of near-field interaction on the performance of beam-space MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and radio frequency (cs.RF). The study also involves numerical simulations and evaluation of error vector magnitude, which falls under the categories of modeling and analysis (cs.MA) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the results, which relates to system engineering (cs.SY).
